@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api
@username = admin
@password = 123456
@basicToken = YWRtaW46Y2hhbmdlX21l
@correlationId = test-correlation-123

### 1) Public health check (no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/ping
Accept: application/json
X-Correlation-Id: {{correlationId}}

### 2) OpenAPI JSON (no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/v3/api-docs
Accept: application/json

### 3) Swagger UI (open in browser)
GET {{baseUrl}}/swagger-ui.html

### 4) Example authenticated request to a protected path
# Replace /secure/example with a real protected endpoint when added.
GET {{baseUrl}}/secure/example
Authorization: Basic {{basicToken}}
Accept: application/json

### 5) Actuator health for monitoring (no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/actuator/health
Accept: application/json

### 6) Actuator info for version/app metadata (no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/actuator/info
Accept: application/json

### 7) Swagger check for production scenario (expect 404/401 if disabled)
# In production profile, app.swagger.enabled is false by default.
GET {{baseUrl}}/v3/api-docs
Accept: application/json

### 8) External LDAP login (auth-service)
POST http://boainhousesys.bankofabyssinia.com:8085/auth-service/api/auth/ldap-login
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
	"username": "your.username",
	"password": "your_password",
	"applicationId": 0
}
